  "release_notes": "Fixes Microsoft Store in-app subscription purchases on Win32 desktop MSIX builds. The Store SDK requires the host to call IInitializeWithWindow.Initialize(hwnd) before any UI-bearing purchase call, but IInitializeWithWindow is classic COM and the Python winrt projection cannot reach it — so direct calls from Python fail with RPC_E_WRONG_THREAD. v1.0.23 ships a tiny C# helper (StoreHelper.exe) bundled alongside the app that performs the IInitializeWithWindow handshake natively and runs the Store call. Also widens the welcome / paywall window so the title and body text no longer clip on smaller default geometries.",
